module: c2-101
level: C2
sequence: 101
slug: advanced-rhetoric
version: '2.0'
title: 'Поглиблена риторика'
subtitle: 'Advanced Rhetoric: The Mechanics of Great Speeches'
content_outline:
- section: Вступ — Від риторики до красномовства
  points:
  - 'State Standard §4.3.5 alignment — rhetoric, argumentation, persuasion, public
    speaking at C2 mastery level'
  - 'Ukrainian oratorical tradition: from Kyiv-Mohyla Academy to parliamentary debate'
  - 'Distinction from C1 persuasive-speech: C2 focuses on ADVANCED figures and their
    compositional interaction'
- section: 'Складні фігури мовлення (Complex Figures of Speech)'
  points:
  - 'Хіазм (chiasmus): mirror structure — Не життя для роботи, а робота для життя'
  - 'Зевгма (zeugma): one verb governing incongruent objects — Він підняв прапор і
    дух армії'
  - 'Оксиморон (oxymoron): contradictory pairing — гірка радість, живий мрець'
  - 'Асиндетон (asyndeton) vs полісиндетон (polysyndeton): rhythm through omission
    or repetition of conjunctions'
  - 'Еліпсис (ellipsis): strategic omission — Ми — за мир. (We are for peace.)'
- section: 'Ритм і композиція промови (Rhythm & Speech Composition)'
  points:
  - 'Tricolon: three-part parallel structure for memorability'
  - 'Антиметабола (antimetabole): reversed repetition — Ask not what your country can
    do for you...'
  - 'Кільцева композиція (ring composition): ending where you began'
  - 'Building to a peroration: the climactic final paragraph'
- section: 'Аналіз великих промов (Analysis of Great Speeches)'
  points:
  - 'Analyze Ukrainian political speeches for rhetorical devices'
  - 'Analyze literary speeches (Franko, Lesya Ukrainka dramatic monologues)'
  - 'Analyze religious oratory (Skovoroda, Mohyla Academy sermons)'
  - 'Compare Ukrainian and Western rhetorical traditions'
- section: 'Практика — Мистецтво промови'
  points:
  - 'Write a speech using at least 5 different rhetorical figures'
  - 'Analyze a transcript: identify ALL figures of speech'
  - 'Rewrite a flat text using rhetorical devices for maximum impact'
  - 'Debate exercise: argue both sides of a proposition'
- section: Підсумок
  points:
  - Complete taxonomy of rhetorical figures with Ukrainian examples
  - Self-assessment checklist for speech effectiveness
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - хіазм (chiasmus) — дзеркальна структура
  - зевгма (zeugma) — одне дієслово, різні об'єкти
  - оксиморон (oxymoron) — поєднання протилежностей
  - асиндетон (asyndeton) — безсполучниковість для ритму
  - полісиндетон (polysyndeton) — багатосполучниковість
  - антиметабола (antimetabole) — зворотне повторення
  - красномовство (eloquence) — мистецтво красномовства
  recommended:
  - перорація (peroration) — завершальна частина промови
  - еліпсис (ellipsis) — стилістичний еліпсис
  - кільцева композиція (ring composition)
  - інвектива (invective) — гостра критика
activity_hints:
- type: quiz
  focus: Identify advanced rhetorical figures
  items: 15
- type: fill-in
  focus: Complete sentences using specific figures
  items: 12
- type: essay-response
  focus: Write a speech with 5+ rhetorical devices
- type: match-up
  focus: Match figure of speech to definition and example
  items: 15
focus: style
pedagogy: Academic
prerequisites:
- c2-100 (C2 Level Completion)
objectives:
- Learner can identify and name advanced rhetorical figures in authentic texts
- Learner can compose speeches using chiasmus, zeugma, and antimetabole
- Learner can analyze the rhetorical structure of political and literary speeches
- Learner can deploy rhetorical devices for maximum persuasive impact
grammar:
- Advanced rhetorical figures (chiasmus, zeugma, oxymoron, antimetabole)
- Asyndeton vs polysyndeton
- Ring composition and peroration
- Interaction of multiple figures in speech composition
register: літературний
immersion: 100% Ukrainian
phase: C2.4 [Meta-Skills & Capstone]
persona:
  voice: Senior Specialist
  role: Professor of Rhetoric
